EECS 461 - MACHINE LEARNING PROJECT INTERIM REPORT

In my project, I will try to predict the genre of the movie using data about movie; like actors, actress, director, screenwriter, duraton of the movie, release date of movie, budget and revenue of movie etc.

At the beginning, for the dataset I will try to collect all the data from Open Movie Database (OMDB) API and The Movie Database(TMDB) API by using request. The Movie Database (TMDb) is a community built movie database and they provide a great application programming interface (API) for accessing information relating to movies as well as ancillary information on reviews, cast members, and genres. The OMDb API is a RESTful web service to obtain movie information, all content and images on the site are contributed and maintained by their users. For accessing TMDb and OMDb API, I need APIkey for both API.

Final Shape of The Datas¶

After parsing all the data about movies from APIs, I planned to have imdbId (as an id), title, budget, overview, revenue, runtime, year, rated, director, writer, actors and all genres as columns.

For feature we can use budget, title, overview, revenue, runtime, year, rated, director (first two director as director1 and director2), writer (first three writer as writer1, writer2, writer3), actor (first five actor as actor1, actor2, actor3, actor4, actor5) and genres (Action, Adventure, Animation, Comedy, Crime, Documentary, Drama, Family, Fantasy, History, Horror, Music, Mystery, Romance, Science Fiction, TV Movie, Thriller, War ,Western)

For text based feature like title and overview; we have to use a method for transforming text to numerical features. Further research will be conducted for it.

url =  "https://api.themoviedb.org/3/movie/24428?api_key="+TMBD_APIKEY
r = requests.get(url)
json_data = r.json()
avengers = {}
for k in json_data.keys():    
    avengers["imdb_id"] = json_data["imdb_id"]
    avengers["title"] = json_data["title"]
    avengers["budget"] = json_data["budget"]
    avengers["overview"] = json_data["overview"]
    avengers["revenue"] = json_data["revenue"]
    avengers["runtime"] = json_data["runtime"]
    avengers["genres"] = json_data["genres"]

url = "http://www.omdbapi.com/?apikey="+OMDB_APIKEY+"&i="+avengers["imdb_id"]
r = requests.get(url)
json_data = r.json()
for k in json_data.keys():
    avengers["year"] = json_data["Year"]
    avengers["rated"] = json_data["Rated"]
    avengers["director"] = ((re.sub(r'\([^)]*\)', '', json_data["Director"])).split(","))
    avengers["writer"] = ((re.sub(r'\([^)]*\)', '', json_data["Writer"])).split(","))
    avengers["actors"] = ((re.sub(r'\([^)]*\)', '', json_data["Actors"])).split(","))
    avengers["imdbrating"] = json_data["imdbRating"]

avengers["writer"] = [x.rstrip() for x in avengers["writer"]]
avengers["writer"] = [x.lstrip() for x in avengers["writer"]]
avengers["actors"] = [x.rstrip() for x in avengers["actors"]]
avengers["actors"] = [x.lstrip() for x in avengers["actors"]]
avengers["director"] = [x.rstrip() for x in avengers["director"]]
avengers["director"] = [x.lstrip() for x in avengers["director"]]
avengers["writer"] = list(set(avengers["writer"]))
avengers["director"] = list(set(avengers["director"]))
avengers["actors"] = list(set(avengers["actors"]))
avengers_genre_temp = avengers["genres"]
del avengers["genres"]
avengers_genre = []

for i in range(1,3,1):
    try:
        avengers["director%s"%(i)] = (avengers["director"][i-1])
    except:
        avengers["director%s"%(i)] = None
for i in range(1,4,1):
    try:
        avengers["writer%s"%(i)] = (avengers["writer"][i-1])
    except:
        avengers["writer%s"%(i)] = None
for i in range(1,6,1):
    try:
        avengers["actor%s"%(i)] = (avengers["actors"][i-1])
    except:
        avengers["actor%s"%(i)] = None
del avengers["actors"]
del avengers["writer"]
del avengers["director"]
for i in avengers_genre_temp:
    avengers_genre.append(i["name"])
avengers_genre
genre_matrix = {}
for i in genres:
    if i in avengers_genre:
        genre_matrix[i] = 1
    if i not in avengers_genre:
        genre_matrix[i] = 0
avengers_genre_df = pd.DataFrame(genre_matrix, index = ["Avengers"])
avengers_df = pd.DataFrame(avengers, index = ["Avengers"])
avengers = pd.concat([avengers_df, avengers_genre_df], axis=1)

I write function that takes tmbd_id as an input and returns movies data as in the example above. But the data set must be large for the efficiency of the results I want to achieve and it is hard to use these APIs because they do not work very stable and there are certain request limits for fixed times.

After a long time on working with these APIs, I noticed that it would be very troublesome to draw thousands of data belonging to the movies, and that I would struggle a lot because of the restriction of these APIs (When you send too many requests, you have a risk of being baned.). Even if everything goes perfect, it took a lot of time to get thousands of movies. So I decided to use these APIs just for simple operations. And, I found a pre-prepared dataset.

Better Dataset¶

I found a dataset that is created from TMDB API and IMDBpy library. It contains approximately 10000 movies. It seperated into three files:

  • First file is actually contains what I want to achieve. (tmdb_id / some information about movies)
  • Second file is about labels. It created from first file. (tmbd_id / genres)
  • Third file fills the missing parts of first file like persons and USA_rating like R, PG13 etc. (tmdb_id / cast, director and writer)

genre_for_freq = genre.drop('tmdb_id', axis=1)
freq_dict = {}
for i in genre_for_freq.columns.values:
    freq_dict[i] = sum(genre_for_freq[i])
In [17]:
pylab.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (11, 11)

movies_for_wordcloud = movies[["tmdb_id","plot"]]
genre_movies_for_wordcloud = genre[["tmdb_id","Action"]]
merged_for_wordcloud = pd.merge(movies_for_wordcloud, genre_movies_for_wordcloud, on='tmdb_id')
merged_for_wordcloud = merged_for_wordcloud[merged_for_wordcloud.Action != 0]
values = " ".join(map(str, (merged_for_wordcloud["plot"].tolist())))
print("Action")
WordCloud(stopwords=final_stopwords,width=1200,height=450).generate(values).to_image()

Evaluation and Future Plans¶

I spent a lot of time trying to create the dataset myself at the beginning of the project. I would have been ahead of my current position if I was dealing with a direct dataset instead of dealing with APIs with a request limit per time period.

I will try to transform the data set into numeric features in the future phases of the project. As can be seen from the wordclouds, movie names and movie summaries have very important values, so I'll try to translate this text-based data into numerical data in order to be able to use them effectively. I will also perform one-hot-encoding to use the people and rating (R, PG13) of movie as we see in "Handling Text and Categorical Attributes" parts in Chapter 2.

Then I will start using different Machine Learning algorithms and evaulate their accuracy.
